AB  - Linear rational expectations models which include `forward-looking' variables typically imply equations of motion with unstable roots. This paper derives a closed form expression for saddlepath restrictions which purge unstable roots from the model's reduced form. It also shows that, for the class of models considered, the reduced form may be written as a finite-order autoregression. An example is provided along with Monte Carlo experiments which demonstrate the gains in estimation accuracy which obtain when the results of this paper are used to concentrate the likelihood function of the model's parameters.
